caption: Wonderful service and such a beautiful lunch spot! We were happy that we could sit outside with our dogs! Delicious ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Great place, enjoyed the seafood and service

My brother and I go to the Paramount Grill for special occasions or for a leisurely Sunday brunch. The entrees are not your standard offerings. The menu offers some unique selections which gets us out of our comfort zone of only eating what we know. The staff are always very pleasant and we never feel rushed.

As for the entrees, we had the scallops, duck, and shrimp/lobster dishes. The scallop dish was by far the best in my opinion. The duck came in close second, and the meat was super tender and cooked to perfection. The service was amazing, the food was unique, and the overall experience was great.
Good food
Fantastic dining experience! Great ambiance with even better food! Thank you Chef
Excellent gourmet restaurant and good service
Fresh ingredients made to perfection everytime. Love their Sunday brunch too!
Truly a 5* experience. Chef is an artist, staff is super friendly. Great place for brunch!
american food and the feeling at this place is super good. normally i would have posted a pic but food looked so good i couldn't stop.
4 stars food, 1 star service.
Excellent food difference desserts made perfect and professional good service I enjoyed the southwest salmon salad for lunch and banana cheese cake
Great food
My fav place for delicious american food. Got there about three, it wasn't crowded. I've had nothing but pleasant experiences here and plan to keep coming back. Prices that are reasonable.
american food and the atmosphere at this location is great. service is always timely even when they have a full house. service is consistently good. the prices are well within reason for the quality.
American food and the scene here is quality. i'll return family next time.
Fancy, food is good
Service was great, food choices limited. Scallops were not cooked well, but salmon was very good. Gouda fondue was top winner for tonight.

Great upscale restaurant with a romantic atmosphere, the food is beautifully plated and delicious. Portions are on the smaller side which I love since I'm usually served way too much food. I would say prices are moderate. They have a great lunch menu as well - this is one of the better places to do a sit-down lunch with colleagues in Gainesville. Haven't had a bad dish here, I've tried everything from soup, salad, fillet, and dessert.
Amazing food. Quick pick up. Great customer service.
Imaginative tasteful meals in elegant simplicity.
Too expensive, I ordered a ceasar salad and it had no dressing and cost close to $10. For $10 I'd appreciate some ceasar on my ceasar salad.
Great food.
Awesome food! Great service!
Although my last experience was not great the owner handled the situation very well and fixed our problems.

I hadn't been to paramount in a while, and decided to go for a birthday dinner with two others. I had called for day-of reservations, which probably wasn't strictly necessary being a mid-week night, but I like to be prepared .I started with a malbec, and we had the panna-rustica with sundried tomatoes, olives, red peppers, and chevre appetizer. The appetizer was quite tasty and the ingredients separated so people who like some arts more than others had an easy time. The server was wonderful, attentive but allowing for a leisurely paced dinner. We waited to put in our entree order until the appetizer came out.

Last night was our second visit.  First time was a B and not especially memorable.  Then a really sweet server who knew nothing about food or wine. Second chance last night.  Server still really nice, but some of same traits as the one the last visit.  Maybe hire or train servers more rigorously?    But the food!  I had an off the menue special of venison which was as excellent as any dish I remember.  It was perfect in every way.  My date had the more standard duck, which delighted her. While my taste confirmed her judgment.
Delicious food, great service
Always the best food. Great ambience and service.

Nothing better than having our evening friends-meetings there, this place makes me optimistic and just happy. I love their salads they are so alive! so delicious and healthy, actually all their food menu is well prepared and offered with care and passion.

Very fresh and delicious food. I had the Salmon Salad and was pleasantly surprised with great flavor considering there wasn't any dressing; just lemon juice and the salmon to flavor the greens. Salmon was cooked perfectly: medium rare.
Very good healthy food and excellent staff
Large portions.

Service is vitally important to a restaurant.  My friend and I were discussing our recent trip to Gainesville and we were talking about which meal was our favorite.  We had so many good ones!  This one was definitely one of the best tasting meals, but the service was so uncaring that it bumped it down two spots.  We reflected on just how important a good server is to your overall experience.

Asked for a negroni, but they didn't have campari, so ended up getting a house cocktail which was decent. Gf got pork chop and I did the diver Scallops. Food was great and I suppose what you would expect at these prices.
Great food in a nice atmosphere

WOW! I am at a loss for words on how to properly explain just how fantastic this restaurant is. First off the customer service was absolutely amazing, very professional, friendly, detail oriented and fairly quick. Now where to start with the food, hands down phenomenal! Literally the best meal I have had in my entire life. I live three and half hours away from this restaurant and I will be driving all that way back just to have another meal here. If you are in Gainsville and looking for somewhere to eat, GO HERE!! You will thank yourself afterwards.
Poor experience - odor from roof leak, soggy & out dated salad, under cooked salmon. Server offered consideration, very hospitable - would not recommend.

I wanna start with that I love civilization. I feel very loyal to them and their brunch but KIDS. Paramount Grill is THE best spot for food in Gainesville. If you want quality, this is it. I came here twice in one week - one for lunch and one for brunch. Both meals were absolutely delightful and both cost $16 - but they both included seafood and I had no qualms with paying for the quality of food that I received.

Appetizer, entrees, and dessert, all amazing. Service was great also. We started with the crab cake app and it was delish. We also got the scallop entree along with the salmon, both were great, but the salmon was unbelievable. We got the creme brulee for dessert and it was so good, we got the cheesecake to take with us! Can't wait to go back, highly recommend.
Great food, service was spotty.  Beautiful location.  Give it a try!
Amazing food. Highly recommend!

While this may be an unlikely location for travelers, this place had zero disappointments. We found this through TripAdvisor, so thanks for all the good honest reviews. This is another one. It was a "can't lose." We ate Sunday brunch at the Paramount Grill. The salmon Benedict, a special, was delicious, as was the mixed greens salad—a mixture of crisp greens, crunchy vegetables and sliced almonds. Service was lovely and attentive.
Nothing 2 write home about. Service was great, food was adequate. Menu is overwritten.
Restaurant had a musty smell upon walking in. Very pricey and entrees just ok.
This place serves really good food.  My wife and I aren't usual on that side of town, yet we always go there for special occasions.
Delicious lunch here. Beet salad and portobello soup in historical building. Nice atmosphere.

Nice atmosphere, good ambience. Never too noisy.Has a variety of dishes that include fresh local vegetables. Also has amazing desserts. The wait staff are informed about the menu and the service is good. The dining experience is consistent and never disappoints. Great place to go for a special occasion or to impress out of town guests with what Gainesville cuisine can offer.

The food was incredible, the staff attentive and courteous. They assisted with table decorations when I was running late at the rehearsal. There was miscommunication with the bar tab and Naheed apologized and worked to resolve the issue with me. The venue is intimate and lovely. I received numerous compliments on the event and wonderful food. I would highly recommend this venue for any event!
great food, intimate setting
Recently, I had the pleasure of dining at the Paramount Grill to celebrate my daughter’s graduation from UF.  The food and service were great.
Really good
Eclectic,  fresh and very tasty. Lots of unexpected flavor combinations

Took my daughter here for her Birthday/Valentine's day.. we are still talking about the food. I wish we had gotten pics of the appetizers. I think that was out favorite part of the meal. It really was a lovely night.
Awesome food quiet atmosphere
Charming decor.  Food was a bit overpriced.
Very good food and beautiful presentation!

I hosted a party of 35 here for my son's rehearsal dinner.   The staff were marvelous, both in getting the event planned and on the evening itself. The night of the event, the staff were so personable and efficient. They really allowed us the space to relax and enjoy the evening.  The food was great and there was a selection for everyone, meat lover to vegan. I heard only good things from my guests.
I ordered the scallops and salad special of the day and was not disappointed. The salad was large and not skimpy as some other places. I done plan on returning.

A perfect place for a romantic dinner or for a group.  Our last visit was for a dear friend's surprise birthday dinner.  There were 8 of us.  The service was excellent and the food is some of the best in Gainesville.  Good place for lunch as well.

Good restaurant with a comfortable yet elegant atmosphere. We went here on Valentine's Day and had the limited menu. The food was good and the service was as well. I wasn't blown away but wasn't disappointed either. The restroom area needs a redesign if it is is to be considered an elegant restaurant.
Great for occasions. Delicious combinations of flavor and an easy going atmosphere. Always an adventure of flavor. You'll pay a little more for it, but it will be worth it!

The food was great! I had a salad with scallops on it for lunch and the cost was rather pricey. It was a huge portion though. The salad wasn't just a plain Jane salad either. It contained asparagus, harecorverts, chick peas, zucchini, tomatoes, carrots, feta cheese, and caramelized red onions with romaine lettuce. The rest of the menu was pretty expensive as well.

There seem to be lots of good places in Gainesville but this one is great. Went for lunch, so we’ll have to go back for dinner. Had the vegetable panano (panini), which was grilled asparagus, red bell pepper, spinach, and pesto. It was yummy and I am not a vegetarian. Also included were their white beans, kalmetta olives, and sun dried tomatoes. Also a home run. My wife had the mushroom bisque which she said was not tasty but I found quite good. She also had their Spinach Caesar which she loved. Service was good but our server spent the first part of our stay talking to another server and laughing. Not good. I am not against comraderi but take it into the kitchen and not out in the restaurant. After I kind of pointed that out, service was great. We’ll go back!
Fantastic food and service! Reasonably priced for a fine dining experience.
Excellent food and service
Always a great meal here. Upscale, quiet, good service.
Not a good experience when the wife and i went for lunch recently.
Well presented delicious food in a nice setting. Most impressive the sound level in the restaurant was conducive to a civil conversation!
Paramount is absolutely my TOP THERE restaurant in the downtown area. The cuisine there is amazing，also the service is great.

The good, the bad, and the ugly. Starting w the good, the food was so delicious and unique it justifies 4 stars. The signature drinks were equally amazing, including the pineapple mojito👌. Their craft beer selection was extensive, although there weren’t any draft selections. The bad, we were 7 minutes late to our reservation and were told they would have to check if they could still take us. When we rounded the corner into the dining area, half the restaurant was empty 🤔. The ugly, my girl ordered the filet and I got the duck. For an app we got the crab cakes. Our food took more than 2 HOURS to come out and the steak was easily well done, as we ordered it Med Rare. I waited another 20 minutes for her steak to come back out before we were both eating. Just to be clear, almost 2.5 hours from the minute we ordered til when we were eating out entree. Now they said they were down a chef, but “so is life”. With a restaurant half full, absolutely inexcusable.  They gave us free drinks and a desert on the house (creme brûlée, which had a hint of butterscotch flavor), which is definitely appreciated. Still, dinner shouldn’t take 4 hours.  Again, I put 4 stars even considering the experience. Food was really good.
Great food and variety for those with dignified taste buds.
Ask for Gary, eat the duck breast!
Always good!
The food is amazing, service is fantasic. Must stop anytime you're in the area.
I've had better food. Service was typical. Clean environment.
This is my go to favorite restaurant in town.  Chef Cliff was doing farm to table style meals before most people knew what is was.  Excellent meals and outstanding service!

5 star food with friendly service. This was our second choice because we couldn’t get into our first choice, and we were thrilled with this happy accident. We’ve eaten at great restaurants throughout the U.S. and abroad, and we both agree this was the best meal we’ve ever had. Not cheap, but worth every penny.  We started with the crab cakes. Didn’t think it could get any better and then it did. My wife had the duck, and I had the angus steak. Our original plan was to split meals, but neither of us was willing to part with our entree’s, and we just shared bites. Each of us feels we made the best choice. We will definitely be back.
Cold hearted people
One of the best restaurants in Gainesville.

This place is top 3 restaurants in Gainesville. A must stop for special occasions. Have gone several times and have never been disappointed (one time they didn’t have the fondue, but it was during graduation season)
Graduation night. Everything was great even though the staff had been working hard all day and night.
Good Food. A little pricey. I wasn't all that impressed.
One of my favorite downtown places to eat. Always fresh food with great service!
Outstanding food, unbelievable
Great food, great service - you can rely on these people
Terrible people.

The restaurant isn't too crowded for lunch but it's a great deal for the level of food. The flavors were amazing and we were surprised by the amount of food that came out. Everyone had to take home leftovers. They have lots of seasonal items and daily specials with lots of in house made touches to the food.

Food was good (I guess that's what really counts) but: Coffee Maker was broken. Restrooms are even worse than at Taco Bell (lines in front, leaky, cold, dirty, clogged up... wow). Tea water was cold (reason: broken coffee maker, no way to cook water otherwise). Service was rushed. Glass was dirty (on the inside). Overall not a good experience unfortunately.
Cliff. Couldn't find your email address but maybe this is it. Last night was fantastic. Wonderful food, friendly professional service and very reasonable prices. THANKS!!!!

We enjoyed the delicous food and atmosphere at Paramount Grille in Gainesville, FL on New Years Eve. Free parking with attendant. The phesant and mahi fish were cooked and served with polenta and veggies. Salads, soups and deserts were fresh with fresh spices and dressings. The bar served wine, beer and mixed drinks.  We would rate it as a 5 star restaurant with excellent chef and staff.
Great food, great service. I enjoyed the duck with ravioli, lemon pie, crab cakes. Looking forward to returning.
Amazing food!

Such a great place to visit and enjoy.  Thanks for the great service, support and quality food.  From wedding parties to anniversaries, luncheons to office parties, and evenings, it's a must visit. The food is absolutely amazing and they even have a new good cocktails.  Thanks!
Excelent food and great service at a good price
Good
We had a great time, the food was prepared beautifully and tasted fresh and fantastic. Great downtown location too! People were friendly, not pretentious.
Excellent.
I was blown away, so great for lunch
Excellent food and service!
Great food, good wine. Vegetarian options are limited but definitely delicious vegetarian dishes for what they do have. Apps are great too!
Great BBQ meals
Tasty and unique food. Very enjoyable
Great atmosphere. Nice cozy environment. Food was exceptional and staff were attentive. Definitely a favorite!
Great Dinner and romantic atmosphere!! My date night was awesome!!
It's got to be the best prepared food in Gainesville.
Great food and service!
Food tasted fresh and delicious.
Good food, well presented and served. Nice setting. Quiet
Service was incredibly slow. My husband order eggs over easy, they came out hard. They don't offer toast and didn't have cream cheese. Worst $30 breakfast ever!!! Wish no stars was available!
Love the variety and quality of dishes. One of the best  to eat in Florida.
Great food, atmosphere, and service! We got there around 6pm on Saturday and there were no lines. Our steak was cooked perfectly and it tasted better than the steak we had at Mark's Steakhouse. 😃

We have been to Paramount Grill many times over the past 12 or more years. This is one of the best restaurants in Gainesville and one of our favorite restaurants. Every time we have been there, the food has been outstanding (brunch or dinner, salads, appetizers, muffins, entrees, desserts, you name it)! Not to mention, the service is phenomenal, Gary is our favorite! When we got engaged, we contacted Clif at Paramount since we wanted to have our wedding rehearsal dinner there. Clif was so helpful throughout the entire process, answered all of our questions and gave us great advice for that night! He even catered to our interests and put their delicious banana cheesecake (our favorite dessert) on the menu for one of the desserts. We had the side room completely to ourselves and our 30 guests. The room was set up perfectly and it was such a comfortable and intimate atmosphere. The food was absolutely delicious, all of our guests raved about how great everything turned out. The wine and beer options were fabulous. And the service was impeccable as always! Highly recommend Paramount for any occasion. We can’t wait to go back for some more delicious food! A true gem!

We chose this restaurant on a recommendation from the Laurel Oak Inn. It was really excellent with a somewhat limited but excellent menu. You'll no doubt run into some unfamiliar selections but they explain it well and we found it very inspired. The service was excellent, attentive but not rushed. Highly recommended!

A bit more on the pricey side but YOU GET WHAT YOU PAY FOR! Great servers and hosts, Paramount also closes for private events! All in all just a lovely place, always so clean and such a nice atmosphere.
Great food! Great service!

For the special occasion, this is my go-to. Consistently delicious, there's nothing else you could ask for. Peaceful ambiance and a great destination if you're looking for a fine-dining establishment.
Brunch is incredible.
It has an invigorating atmosphere. The food is great, granted I was with good company. I'm willing to go back again. It is good for groups.
Beat fine cuisine in Gainesville hands down.

Everything on the menu looked great, and the food we ordered lived up to the description.  Nice white tablecloths, reasonably quiet, and our table by the window had a beautiful view of live oak trees in the parking lot.  They have free valet parking, which was wonderful!
Best food in Gainesville.
We've only been for brunch but we go there often. Some of the best drip coffee around!

Went for Sunday brunch and was very impressed with the quality of the food and pleased with the prices. I tried the Crab Cake Benedict and a Poached egg Roasted Pork special. Both were excellently prepared, everything tasted very high quality. I didn't love the toast in place of an English muffin on the Benedict, but that is just personal preference I suppose. Overall, I can't wait to go back.
A Must Try... I had the Angus Fillet... It was amazing.
Lovely food and ambience. And I was appreciative that they treated a solitary female diner well. Quiet classy place for an excellent meal.

The hard wood floors and high ceilings of this transitionally designed restaurant create an exciting atmosphere. The rooms fill with the echoes of neighboring dinner tables small talk conversations, and the lighting is enough to fill the room while simultaneously creating visual space between your table and the other customers. The menu unintentionally communicates the sophistication of a traditional French restaurant, there are more wines and beers to choose from than any sane person would have the time to read through yet the food choices can be counted on your left palm. Don't be fooled though, each dish is a perfect blend of spices, carbohydrates, proteins and the chiefs quirky creativity. The service is like a well oiled machine, as the servers pace through the rooms delivering food and drinks they provide quick no fuss service. Overall a great experience.

Great environment and a beautiful restaurant. The menu is diverse but it does not deliver. The food is bland and the quality mediocre for the price. Beside the food, the ambiance was on point, it really is a nice environment for a date.
This place has great food!  Love the cuisine.  I will eat here often.
Very nice

We hosted a Rehearsal Dinner with a multi-course meal, wine, and beer (all included) and experienced THE best meal we could have imagined possible.  We had a private room that had a wonderful decor, an incredible staff of servers that did their jobs in a highly effective manner without any disruption to the party.  The food was served in a timely manner and was "hot"...we have no idea how they managed to produce so many dishes within and serve within minutes to a group of 35 individuals.  The entrees included an awesome duck, a filet that melted in your mouth, and an Ahi tuna that was cooked to perfection.  I appreciate the way the servers recognized times when toasts were being made - they ensured the glasses were filled and then stepped out of the room to provide privacy as appropriate.  In addition to the entrees, we had two appetizers, including a crab cake (to die for) , a choice of two salads, and two desserts.  Everything was done to PERFECTION...Period...it simply could not have been better...although I think I could have eaten about 4 or 5 of the creme brulee deserts...wow.  Finally, we want to recognize the ease of working with Chef Nelson...he was extremely good to work with, he returned phone calls in a timely manner and/or emailed whichever was best at the time.  He made it so easy to host this event and we felt as though the price was exceptional for what we were served.  In closing, we looked into a number of locations to host our dinner and did not find any place that offered the privacy and decor provided by the Paramount Grill.  The Chef was amazing to work with, the food was STELLAR, and the staff was magnificent.  Our dining experience was EXCEPTIONAL...Thank you to everyone there for your hard work, attention to detail, and sincere motivation to make our dining experience everything we dreamed it would be.
My wife and I went here for our anniversary dinner last month. Both food and presentation were excellent, and a great value for the price.
Superb place for a relaxing lunch.  Unque menu, wonderful ambiance and great service.   One of my favorite Gainesville spots.
